    • Constructor Detail

      • Trade

        public Trade(java.lang.String traderA,
             java.lang.String traderB,
             java.util.List<Item> traderAItemsToTrade,
             java.util.List<Item> traderBItemsToTrade,
             java.time.LocalDateTime startDate)
        Creates a trade with an item that both the seller wants to sell and the buyer wants to buy. The buyer creates the trade with the item that they want to sell.
        Parameters:
        traderA - takes in a entities.trader that wants to create the entities.Trade.
        traderB - takes in a entities.trader that wants to borrow the item based on the trade.
        traderAItemsToTrade - takes in items that tradeA own and want to be borrowed to traderB.
        traderBItemsToTrade - takes in items that tradeB own and want to be borrowed to traderA.
        startDate - is a LocalDateTime type that indicates the start date of a Trade. Note: this is also used to identify the rental process if the trade is temporary.
